(3,1,'2026-02-02','2026-02-06','{"monday":{"task":"Orientation to KEMRI Health Economics & Research Methods Unit","comment":"Professional and research-ready attitude"},"tuesday":{"task":"Reviewed current health economic evaluation studies and biostatistical methodologies","comment":"Good command of research methodology"},"wednesday":{"task":"Assisted in data cleaning for the malaria treatment cost-effectiveness study","comment":"Data cleaning is systematic and accurate"},"thursday":{"task":"Participated in KEMRI IRB ethical review meeting as an observer","comment":"Good exposure to research ethics process"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted first logbook with detailed research orientation reflection","comment":"Reflective and academically strong entry"}}','Approved','2026-02-02','Faith demonstrates exceptional research aptitude and a strong biostatistical background. Excellent start.','Faith''s data cleaning accuracy was remarkable. The lead researcher has assigned her a sub-study.','2026-02-06 17:00:00'),
(3,2,'2026-02-09','2026-02-13','{"monday":{"task":"Developed a Markov state-transition model for HIV treatment cost-effectiveness in R","comment":"Advanced actuarial modeling applied to health economics"},"tuesday":{"task":"Calibrated the Markov model using published clinical trial data","comment":"Model calibration is methodologically sound"},"wednesday":{"task":"Conducted probabilistic sensitivity analysis on the HIV model","comment":"Sensitivity analysis is comprehensive"},"thursday":{"task":"Presented Markov model findings to the health economics team","comment":"Presentation was technically impressive"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook with detailed model development reflection","comment":"Reflection shows exceptional analytical depth"}}','Approved','2026-02-09','Faith''s Markov model for HIV cost-effectiveness is of research paper quality. Extraordinary work.','The health economics lead has included Faith as a contributing author on the KEMRI research paper.','2026-02-13 17:00:00'),
(3,3,'2026-02-16','2026-02-20','{"monday":{"task":"Performed survival analysis on tuberculosis patient data using Kaplan-Meier estimation in STATA","comment":"Survival analysis is methodologically correct"},"tuesday":{"task":"Interpreted survival curves and hazard ratios for the TB treatment team","comment":"Clinical interpretation is accurate"},"wednesday":{"task":"Attended a WHO health technology assessment workshop as KEMRI representative","comment":"Good representation at the WHO workshop"},"thursday":{"task":"Summarized WHO HTA framework findings for KEMRI research team","comment":"Summary report is comprehensive"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook and documented TB survival analysis methodology","comment":"Methodology documentation is publication-ready"}}','Approved','2026-02-16','Representing KEMRI at a WHO workshop is an extraordinary achievement for an attachment student.','WHO workshop organizers praised the quality of Faith''s questions and contributions. Phenomenal.','2026-02-20 17:00:00'),
(3,4,'2026-02-23','2026-02-27','{"monday":{"task":"Built a disease burden model for COVID-19 long-term sequelae using R Shiny","comment":"Interactive model is functional and user-friendly"},"tuesday":{"task":"Validated the R Shiny model with epidemiological data from the Kenya NHIF","comment":"Validation results are statistically robust"},"wednesday":{"task":"Presented the COVID-19 burden model to the KEMRI Director of Research","comment":"Director praised the model''s policy relevance"},"thursday":{"task":"Submitted the model technical report to the KEMRI publications committee","comment":"Committee accepted report for internal publication"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook and monthly progress report to academic supervisor","comment":"Monthly report is of academic paper quality"}}','Approved','2026-02-23','Faith''s R Shiny disease burden model has been accepted for KEMRI internal publication. Extraordinary.','KEMRI Director described Faith as the most capable intern the institute has hosted in five years.','2026-02-27 17:00:00'),
(3,5,'2026-03-02','2026-03-06','{"monday":{"task":"Conducted a systematic literature review on maternal mortality costs in Sub-Saharan Africa","comment":"Literature review is comprehensive, 45 papers reviewed"},"tuesday":{"task":"Applied GRADE evidence quality framework to the literature findings","comment":"GRADE application is methodologically correct"},"wednesday":{"task":"Developed a cost-of-illness model for maternal mortality interventions","comment":"Cost-of-illness model is well-structured"},"thursday":{"task":"Attended KEMRI weekly research seminar and presented literature review findings","comment":"Presentation was highly commended by KEMRI senior researchers"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook and literature review for research team review","comment":"Review accepted for the KEMRI library database"}}','Approved','2026-03-02','Faith''s systematic review has been accepted for the KEMRI institutional repository. Remarkable output.','KEMRI Senior Researchers have recommended Faith for the research innovation award at the annual gala.','2026-03-06 17:00:00'),
(3,6,'2026-03-09','2026-03-13','{"monday":{"task":"Began drafting a peer-reviewed journal article on actuarial methods in health economics for KEMRI","comment":"Article draft shows strong academic writing skills"},"tuesday":{"task":"Incorporated research team feedback into journal article draft","comment":"Revisions applied accurately and promptly"},"wednesday":{"task":"Submitted article to KEMRI research publications review committee","comment":"Submitted for peer review consideration"},"thursday":{"task":"Worked on a policy brief on universal health coverage financing for the Ministry of Health","comment":"Policy brief is evidence-based and actionable"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook with reflection on research publication experience","comment":"Reflection demonstrates professional research maturity"}}','Approved','2026-03-09','Faith has submitted a journal article for peer review. This is unprecedented for an attachment student.','We have submitted Faith''s policy brief to the Ministry of Health. The impact of her work is national.','2026-03-13 17:00:00'),
(3,7,'2026-03-16','2026-03-20','{"monday":{"task":"Completed actuarial review of KEMRI''s health insurance product actuarial assumptions","comment":"Actuarial review is technically sound"},"tuesday":{"task":"Prepared a pricing recommendation report for NHIF scheme sustainability","comment":"Pricing recommendations are evidence-based"},"wednesday":{"task":"Presented NHIF pricing findings to the KEMRI Director and Ministry representative","comment":"Ministry representative requested a detailed follow-up briefing"},"thursday":{"task":"Worked on the follow-up briefing document for the Ministry of Health","comment":"Briefing document is policy-grade quality"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook and collected academic supervisor endorsement","comment":"Endorsement obtained with highest commendation"}}','Approved','2026-03-16','Faith''s NHIF pricing work has reached the Ministry of Health. A student''s impact at a national level.','Ministry of Health representative has requested Faith to present at a national health financing forum.','2026-03-20 17:00:00'),
(3,8,'2026-03-23','2026-03-27','{"monday":{"task":"Presented at the National Health Financing Forum as KEMRI representative","comment":"Presentation was broadcast on KBC Health Channel"},"tuesday":{"task":"Participated in post-forum panel discussion on actuarial methods in public health","comment":"Panel discussion was nationally televised"},"wednesday":{"task":"Completed all handover documentation for the health economics models developed","comment":"Models documented and transferred to KEMRI repository"},"thursday":{"task":"Prepared final attachment report incorporating all supervision feedback","comment":"Final report is of PhD dissertation quality"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook and presented final attachment report to academic supervisor","comment":"Supervisor described report as exceptional"}}','Approved','2026-03-23','Faith presented at a nationally televised health financing forum. An unprecedented achievement.','Faith represented KEMRI with distinction on national television. We are enormously proud of her.','2026-03-27 17:00:00'),
(3,9,'2026-03-30','2026-04-03','{"monday":{"task":"Finalized journal article revisions based on internal peer review feedback","comment":"Article is now ready for journal submission"},"tuesday":{"task":"Formally submitted the journal article to the East African Medical Journal","comment":"Submission confirmed by journal editorial team"},"wednesday":{"task":"Collected all clearance signatures from KEMRI department heads","comment":"Clearance obtained smoothly"},"thursday":{"task":"Conducted final knowledge transfer session with KEMRI health economics team","comment":"Knowledge transfer recognized as thorough and impactful"},"friday":{"task":"Submitted logbook and attended KEMRI farewell ceremony for interns","comment":"Received the KEMRI Outstanding Intern Award"}}','Approved','2026-03-30','Faith received the KEMRI Outstanding Intern Award - a recognition given to one intern per year.','We are submitting Faith for consideration for the national Top Intern of the Year award.','2026-04-03 17:00:00'),
(3,10,'2026-04-06','2026-04-08','{"monday":{"task":"Completed all university exit documentation and submitted clearance form","comment":"All clearances finalized"},"tuesday":{"task":"Participated in university post-attachment debrief session for the cohort","comment":"Led the group debrief with great insight"},"wednesday":{"task":"Completed online university attachment evaluation survey","comment":"Detailed and outstanding evaluation submitted"},"thursday":{"task":"N/A - Good Friday Public Holiday","comment":""},"friday":{"task":"N/A - Easter Monday Public Holiday","comment":""}}','Approved','2026-04-06','Faith has completed the most impactful attachment in our department''s history. A phenomenal student.','KEMRI-level clearance secured. She leaves behind a published journal article bearing her name.','2026-04-08 17:00:00'),
(3,11,'2026-04-13','2026-04-17','{"monday":{"task":"Attended faculty awards ceremony and received Outstanding Attachment Student award","comment":"Well-deserved recognition from faculty"},"tuesday":{"task":"Submitted physical attachment documents to department attachments office","comment":"All physical requirements fulfilled promptly"},"wednesday":{"task":"Post-attachment academic counselling session with department chairperson","comment":"Chairperson recommends Faith for PhD scholarship"},"thursday":{"task":"Finalized all remaining university portal submissions","comment":"University portal submissions confirmed"},"friday":{"task":"Attachment formally concluded by university coordinator","comment":"Coordinator described Faith as a model attachment student"}}','Approved','2026-04-13','Faith received the faculty Outstanding Attachment Student award. The department is enormously proud.','KEMRI will provide a full letter of recommendation for Faith''s graduate school applications.','2026-04-17 17:00:00'),
(3,12,'2026-04-22','2026-04-25','{"monday":{"task":"Post-attachment academic session and final documentation review","comment":"All documentation verified and complete"},"tuesday":{"task":"Collected degree programme coordinator''s attachment endorsement letter","comment":"Endorsement letter received"},"wednesday":{"task":"Filed all attachment records in the faculty attachment management system","comment":"All records filed and confirmed"},"thursday":{"task":"Attachment officially complete - all requirements fulfilled","comment":"Final confirmation issued by attachments office"},"friday":{"task":"N/A - Attachment period concluded","comment":""}}','Approved','2026-04-22','Faith Jepchirchir is the outstanding attachment student of the year. A truly exceptional scholar.','KEMRI looks forward to Faith''s return as a full researcher. A once-in-a-generation talent.','2026-04-25 17:00:00');

